 The UDF Investor Center is the resource for investors in United Development Funding I, United Development Funding III, United Development Funding IV, and United Development Funding V who believe they lost money as a result of their investments in UDF programs. This website is not affiliated with UDF.
Recent blog postings by a renowned hedge fund manager who predicted the 2008 subprime debacle alleged that UDF is using new investor money to pay existing investors in Ponzi-like fashion, while UDF management is misleading investors. The allegations pertain to the UDF I, UDF III, UDF IV, and UDF V programs. Recent class actions on behalf of some investors in UDF IV make similar allegations as to that program.
The Peiffer Rosca Wolf law firm’s securities lawyers, Alan Rosca and Joe Peiffer, have been investigating UDF offerings to investors, and are preparing to take action and seek compensation on behalf of UDF investors. The focus of their cases is different from the recent class actions.
UDF investors, including investors who invested prior to June 2014, are encouraged to contact attorneys Alan Rosca or Joe Peiffer for more information or a free, no-obligation discussion about this matter, at 888-998-0520, by email at arosca@prwlegal.com, or through the contact form on this website. 

 



